-- Absa Capital’s NewGold ETF Lists on the Nigerian Bourse
-- B y   V i n c e n t   N w a n m a
-- 2011-12-19T16:49:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-19/absa-capital-s-newgold-etf-lists-on-the-nigerian-bourse-1-.html
Absa Capital, the corporate and
investment banking unit of  Absa Group Ltd. (ASA) , listed its NewGold
Exchange Traded Fund on the Nigeria Stock Exchange today, the
bourse said.  “This is the first of many exchange traded funds to
come,” Oscar Onyema, chief executive officer of the  Nigerian
Stock Exchange , told reporters today in Lagos, the commercial
capital. Several other applications have been received and are
being considered, he said.  The stock exchange of sub-Saharan Africa’s second-biggest
economy will introduce options by 2013 and futures by 2015, as
part of its plan to increase the number of traded securities and
deepen the local  capital market .  Absa Capital will work in Nigeria with Vetiva Capital
Management Ltd., a Lagos-based brokerage, Basile Ngomane of
Absa, told reporters.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Nwanma in Lagos at 
 vnwanma@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
